Package de.nec.nle.siafu.exceptions

This package contains all the simulation exceptions

See:
          Description

Exception Summary
AgentNotFoundException Exception thrown when an agent that is being searched by name, can not be found.
GUINotReadyException This exception is thrown when a component tries to issue a command to the GUI, but the GUI has not finished loading a simulation.
InfoFieldsLockedException Exception thrown when trying to add new keys to the info field of an agent.
InfoUndefinedException Exception thrown when trying to retrieve a variable from the info field, but the key doesn't match any of the existing maps.
InitializationRequiredException Thrown when a class that needs initialization is invoqued before the initialize method has completed.
InvalidFlatDataException Thrown when parsing a flat data that does not conform to the appropriate format for the class it represents.
NothingNearException Exception thrown to indicate that there is nothing near the position that has been searched.
PlaceNotFoundException This exception is thrown when a place is searched by name, and not found.
PlacesTypeIsEmptyException This exception is thrown when trying to retrieve places of a given type, but there aren't any at all.
PlaceTypeUndefinedException This exception is thrown when requesting places of a type that does not exist.
PositionOnAWallException This exception is thrown when attempting to move the agent on a wall.
PositionOutOfTheMapException This exception is thrown when attempting to create a position that is outside the map area.
PositionUnreachableException This exception is thrown when pointing the agent to a valid position which the agent can not reach, because there is no path that leads to it.
TrackableNotFoundException Exception thrown when an agent or place (i.e.
UnexistingSpriteException Thrown when a sprite change is requested for an agent, but the sprite is not available in this simulation.
UnknownContextException This exception is thrown when retrieving a context variable which does not exist.
